    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lankan youth arrested in Chennai",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Chief Commissioner of Airport Customs received confidential information that a large amount of contraband was being brought to Chennai Meenambakkam International Airport.",
        "After this, the customs officials secretly monitored the passengers. At that time, the passengers traveling on the flight from Colombo to Chennai were seriously searched.",
        "In it, a youth named Naimuddin (28 years old) from Sri Lanka was stopped and questioned on suspicion. Then they searched his belongings as he contradicted himself. There is nothing wrong with it. But a scan of him revealed that he had swallowed small packets of gemstones.",
        "They then gave him a treat and when he took them out they found 56 small packets of glittering gemstones. Then they classified them.",
        "Subsequently, they confiscated 1,746 gemstones worth Rs.94 lakh 34 thousand with 8 thousand 309 carats.",
        "Following this, the authorities arrested the Sri Lankan youth who was smuggling precious stones, who is behind the smuggling of precious stones? They are investigating."
      ],
